The Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has suspended Rochas Okorocha, former governor of Imo State. In a letter seen by Daily Trust, Governor Mai Mala Buni, Chairman of the Caretaker Committee, and John Akpanudoedehe, its Secretary, based Okorocha’s suspension on anti-party activities. “This is to communicate to you, the National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) Party ratification of your suspension by the Imo State Chapter of our great party for anti-party activities,” the letter read. “The suspension follows after the recommendation by the Imo State Disciplinary Committee set up to investigate allegations of gross anti-party activities against you which is in line with Article 21 (B) I-VI of our party’s constitution.”  